The paper discusses the formal design of human-robot collaboration (HRC) with respect to high-level complex missions, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a Bayesian non-parametric learning approach for POMDP model learning, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the psychology studies that suggest Markovian properties of human behaviors, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed learning method in a driver-assistance test-bed, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
